LARAMIE, Wyo.
(AP) -- In the weeks after the beating death of gay   student Matthew Shepard, this college town found itself portrayed  as backwards, homophobic, an outpost of Wild West-style violence  and small-mindedness.
With the first of Shepard's alleged attackers set to go on trial   for his life Wednesday, those images of Laramie could work to  prosecutors' advantage.
